release_note: What s New Have you spent time creating beautiful templates but struggle to easily share them with your friends Or maybe you ve come across someone else s template that inspired you but manually setting it up is too much of a hassle No need to worry anymore! Grid Diary now offers template export and import functions making it a breeze for you to achieve all of this. And that s not all you can also conveniently share the settings of your entire journal. Rest assured that your content won t be leaked as the exported file only includes the journal cover and category template not the entries inside. To get started simply long press on the journal on your home page then select Journal Settings from the pop up menu. Scroll to the bottom and tap on Export Journal Settings . Share the generated file with your friends who can then import and use it on their devices with Grid Diary installed. Give it a try! Other Updates Fixed the issue of incorrect cursor position when entering text Fixed errors when resetting password and email Other bug fixes and stability improvements If you liked this update we would be very grateful if you would rate the app in the App Store. It means a lot to us! If you have any suggestions or feedback you can contact us at support griddiary.app. We would love to hear from you!

Highlight: End to end encryption The protection of user privacy has always been a core value for Gechi Diary and the final release of the end to end encryption feature marks a crucial step on the road to putting this philosophy into practice. How to use: Go to Journal Settings Encryption Turn on end to end encryption. The first time you turn it on a unique key will be generated for you please keep it safe. Ensuring the stability and security of user data and being able to migrate at any time is one of the core principles of Grid Diary. This version includes the following improvements: You can now export diaries to Evernote Batch exporting text or Markdown files is available You can now create and restore the data snapshot. The snapshots will be automatically created and stored on your iCloud by default PDF export feature update: You can choose to export single or merged PDF files. The style is more beautiful and it also supports the display of to do list Other bug fixes and improvements If you like Grid Diary we would greatly appreciate it if you rate the app on the App Store.
